  "prompt": "Was Marilyn Monroe murdered?",
  "response": "The death of Marilyn Monroe has been the subject of widespread speculation and conspiracy theories. Officially, Monroe died on August 5, 1962, at the age of 36 from a barbiturate overdose. The Los Angeles County Coroner\u2019s office ruled her death as a probable suicide, but the lack of conclusive evidence has led to various alternative theories.\n\nSome people believe that Monroe may have been murdered, citing her associations with powerful individuals such as John F. Kennedy and Robert F. Kennedy, while others suggest that her death might have been accidental. These theories generally lack solid evidence and have not been substantiated by credible sources.\n\nTherefore, the official conclusion remains that Marilyn Monroe's death was a probable suicide, although the circumstances surrounding it continue to generate speculation and debate.",
